\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Systematic comparison with most similar LLM-based NAS and optimization methods. NAS target: method aims at neural architecture search; Unconstrained search space: search over executable code rather than predefined cell encodings or fixed discrete spaces; Automated failure diagnosis: structured modeling of code execution failures (e.g., diagnostic triples) as first-class feedback signals; Single-GPU ($\leq $24\,GB): demonstrated effective with $\leq $7B LLMs on a single consumer GPU; No LLM fine-tuning: operates with frozen pretrained LLMs without any parameter updates. Our method uniquely combines all five dimensions.}}{4}{table.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{table:comparison}{{1}{4}{Systematic comparison with most similar LLM-based NAS and optimization methods. NAS target: method aims at neural architecture search; Unconstrained search space: search over executable code rather than predefined cell encodings or fixed discrete spaces; Automated failure diagnosis: structured modeling of code execution failures (e.g., diagnostic triples) as first-class feedback signals; Single-GPU ($\leq $24\,GB): demonstrated effective with $\leq $7B LLMs on a single consumer GPU; No LLM fine-tuning: operates with frozen pretrained LLMs without any parameter updates. Our method uniquely combines all five dimensions}{table.caption.7}{}}
\newlabel{table:comparison@cref}{{[table][1][]1}{[1][3][]4}}
